, "documentation": ["R interval.\n\nAn R interval is an 1-start, fully-closed one. It means that:\n- The elements of a sequence have the coordinates `1, 2, 3, ...`.\n- An interval `RInterval(start, stop)` is defined by the coordinates\n  `start, start+1, ..., stop-1, stop`.\n\nAttributes\n----------\nstart\n    Start of interval. Valid values are `1, 2, ..., stop`.\nstop\n    End of interval. Valid values are `start, start+1, ...`."]}], "exports": [{"name": "deciphon_intervals.Interval", "xref": {"fqname": "deciphon_intervals.Interval", "project": null}}, {"name": "deciphon_intervals.PyInterval", "xref": {"fqname": "deciphon_intervals.PyInterval", "project": null}}, {"name": "deciphon_intervals.RInterval", "xref": {"fqname": "deciphon_intervals.RInterval", "project": null}}]}]}